                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281023-75-off446 t18281023-75-crimeloc448"></join>, feloniously did falsely make, forge, and counterfeit, a certain order for payment of money
            </rs>, as follows:</p>
               <p>Messrs. Hankey and Co. London, August 23, 1828.</p>
               <p>Pay to Mr. Ibbottson, or bearer, the sum of sixty-four pounds, ten shillings.</p>

               <p>Â£64. 10s. THOMAS TAYLOR. with intention to defrand 
